HEADWORD: Amyl
<hw>Am"yl</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>am</ets>ylum
starch + <ets>-yl</ets>. Cf. <er>Amidin</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>A univalent hydrocarbon radical, <chform>C5H11</chform>, of the
paraffine series found in amyl alcohol or fusel oil, etc.</def>⟦br⟧
